Maybe it's just that it's Monday....  And the rain caught me about 100 yards from the house.  Discovered I can still jog if I have to.

@Mar in PA 
It depends on your definition of 'well-read.' I read a good amount of historical fiction, where the sheriff is always raising the HUE AND CRY, summoning all the able-bodied men of the village to chase down a murder suspect. Spoiler alert: it's always the wrong man, but no worries, Brother Cadfael will find the real killer.

But I've probably never read any of the 'fashionable' books on Oprah's book club, so I didn't know that the main character of Everything, Everywhere, All at Once was an IRS agent last week.

@Grant 

Aha, I was trying to think of something for Saab/sob, also.

We once had a grey cat with startling green eyes, adopted from the local shelter. Her previous owner had named her Wasabi. Not sure if that was for her green eyes or because she thought she was hot stuff. We kept the name, it fit.

@Red Carpet 
Yes, I found LYRE an odd entry--I connect lyres with ancients like David and Orpheus, and lutes with Medieval troubadours. However, organologists--yes, it is a profession--think otherwise, and place the Lyre in a subfamily (Yoked Lutes) within the greater "Lute family"--which also includes "Bowed Lutes", i.e. Violins etc.

Here a lute, there a lute, everywhere a lute-lute.

@Dollie J 
There is a Jurassic Park themed tour agency in Hawaii that conducts tours of what it describes as all the filming sites for all the movies. Their list includes ten different locations of which one is on Maui, three are on Oahu, and six are on KAUAI. The filming of the original  film began on  8/24/1992 on that island. On 9/11/1992  Hurricane Iniki made a direct hit on KAUAI, costing them a full day of shooting. To see the tour locations:

<a href="https://tinyurl.com/3u5tze5v" target="_blank">https://tinyurl.com/3u5tze5v</a>

